SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0

This project is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

Why Apache-2.0 (decided as part of Phase 3, per
open-source-project-structure.md §7): it's the more common choice when
the explicit goal is a "reusable framework others build upon" (your
words, from the Phase 1 requirements) rather than a self-hosted service
you want to prevent closed-source competitors from forking - that's the
AGPL-3.0 case instead. Apache-2.0 also includes an explicit patent grant,
which plain MIT doesn't. Revisit this if that goal changes.

